Environmental Factors



Machinery may produce noise levels that exceed OSHA's action level: Employees are provided with and required to wear personal hearing protection devises in these areas;
All employees are provided with and required to wear safety glasses, steel-toed shoes, and 100% cotton uniforms;


Essential Functions



Manipulation requirements: (Hands or Feet): This position requires an individual to constantly perform one and/or all of the following movements/functions: Handle, reach, feel perform fine motor manipulations with their hands, and perform gross motor manipulations involved in moving materials.

Provide accurate estimates for scope of work/prices for all manufactured components/assemblies through the manufacturing department:
Provide support through proper information utilizing outside vendors for any material/hardware pricing and ensuring that all estimates reflect current and precise quoting on the scope of work outlined;
Thoroughly comprehend the Bill of Materials (BOMs) and have a strong understanding of any required special outside processes;
Utilization of CAD software to review sales and engineering drawings.
